# Frontend architecture (K-Lab SSO Shell)

Follow [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) for full guidelines. Non-negotiables:

## `app/` — thin routes only

- `page.tsx` files **only** import and render a View from `ui/{context}/views/`.
- No inline UI markup or business logic in pages.
- Layout wiring: `app/layout.tsx` + `app/providers.tsx`; shell chrome lives in `ui/shell/containers/`.

## `ui/` — presentation by context

| Kind | Path |
|------|------|
| View | `ui/{context}/views/{Name}/{Name}View.tsx` |
| Container | `ui/{context}/containers/{Name}/` |
| Feature component | `ui/{context}/components/` |
| Cross-feature component | `ui/shared/components/` |
| Provider (React context) | `ui/{context}/providers/` or `ui/shared/providers/` |
| Hook | `ui/{context}/hooks/use{Feature}.ts` |

Shell: `ui/shell/`. Auth & login: `ui/user-management/`. Shared chrome: `ui/shared/`.

## `contexts/` — business logic only

- Domain: `contexts/{context}/domain/`
- Application services: `contexts/{context}/application/{entity}.service.ts` → return `Result<T>` when adding new services
- Infrastructure: `contexts/{context}/infrastructure/`
- **No React** in `contexts/`. No UI imports from `contexts/`.

## Shell-specific

- `config/` — app registry, dashboard copy, auth brand config (static, not DI)
- `lib/` — navigation resolution, presence session, krisk dev proxy

## When adding features

1. Thin page in `app/`
2. View composes containers/components
3. Hook calls application service (prefer DI container when registered; facade OK for auth until then)
4. New domain logic stays under `contexts/{context}/`, not in views
